result_part1 = pd.DataFrame()
for y in k.Year.unique():
    tmp = k[k['Year'] == y]
    total = k[k['Year'] == y]['Total_Sales'].sum()
    tmp.loc[:, 'Ratio'] = tmp.loc[:, 'Total_Sales'] / total
    result_part1 = result_part1.append(tmp)

ax.legend(bbox_to_anchor=(1.05, 1), loc='upper left')
ax.axhline(1, color='black', linestyle='-', linewidth='2')
for rect in ax.patches:
    # Find where everything is located
    height = rect.get_height()
    width = rect.get_width()
    x = rect.get_x()
    y = rect.get_y()
    
    # The width of the bar is also not pixels, it's the
    # number of animals. So we can use it as the label!
    label_text = round(height, 2)
    
    # ax.text(x, y, text)
    label_x = x + width / 2
    label_y = y + height / 2
    if height > 0: 
        ax.text(label_x, label_y, label_text, ha='center', va='center')
